tasks.description:
Create the presentational floating-panel primitive at `apps/client/src/layers/shared/ui/floating-panel.tsx`. It is a controlled component: geometry lives entirely in props, the primitive owns gesture mechanics only, and it must not import the app store, `useAppStore`, or any router hook â€” verify with `grep -n "app-store\|react-router" apps/client/src/layers/shared/ui/floating-panel.tsx` returning nothing.

Export exactly these types and the component, matching this shape verbatim:

```tsx
export interface FloatingPanelGeometry {
  x: number;
  y: number;
  width: number;
  height: number;
}

export interface FloatingPanelProps {
  title: string;
  geometry: FloatingPanelGeometry;
  onGeometryChange: (g: FloatingPanelGeometry) => void;
  onClose: () => void;
  /** Renders a restore control when provided (e.g. \"send back inline\"). */
  onRestore?: () => void;
  minWidth?: number; // default 280
  minHeight?: number; // default 180
  children: React.ReactNode;
  className?: string;
}

export function FloatingPanel(props: FloatingPanelProps): React.ReactNode
```

Also export a pure helper `export function clampGeometry(geometry: FloatingPanelGeometry, minWidth: number, minHeight: number): FloatingPanelGeometry` used internally by the primitive (and directly unit-testable). It must: cap `width`/`height` to at least `minWidth`/`minHeight` and at most `window.innerWidth - 16` / `window.innerHeight - 16` (the 8px-per-edge viewport margin called out in the goals); clamp `x` to `[0, Math.max(0, window.innerWidth - width)]` and `y` to `[0, Math.max(0, window.innerHeight - height)]` so the panel is always fully reachable inside the viewport.

Rendering and mechanics:
- Portal to `document.body` via `createPortal`. Root container: `fixed z-40` â€” this repo's `z-40` convention is the embedded sidebar backdrop (`apps/client/src/App.tsx:108`, `className="absolute inset-0 z-40 bg-black/40"`), which sits below the Radix portal layer's uniform `z-50` (dialogs, popovers, sheets, menus) â€” confirm with `grep -rn "z-50" apps/client/src/layers/shared/ui/dialog.tsx` â€” so modals correctly cover the mini-player while it floats above ordinary content and sticky chrome.
- Header: drag region containing the truncated `title` (`truncate min-w-0`) plus icon controls â€” a close button (always) and a restore button (only rendered when `onRestore` is provided). Each control gets an `aria-label` ("Close" / "Restore") and is sized `size-(--size-icon-sm)`.
- Drag gesture: follow the document-listener pointer pattern used by `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/ui/ScrollThumb.tsx` (`handleThumbPointerDown`, lines ~92-129) â€” on the header's `onPointerDown`, call `e.preventDefault()`, stash the starting pointer position and starting geometry in refs, and attach `pointermove`/`pointerup` listeners to `document` (not `setPointerCapture` â€” match the existing drag precedents in this codebase, which use the document-listener pattern). During `pointermove`, apply the live delta IMPERATIVELY to the container's inline transform/style via the ref (rAF-throttled, mirroring `ScrollThumb`'s direct `el.scrollTop` write and `DevToolsPanel`'s drag-resize in `apps/client/src/main.tsx:73-100`) â€” do NOT call `onGeometryChange` on every frame; that would defeat the performance goal below. On `pointerup` or `pointercancel`, compute the final clamped geometry (via `clampGeometry`) and call `onGeometryChange` exactly once with it, then remove the `document` listeners. This is the single source of truth for the "write on pointerup, not per-frame" performance goal â€” the store's `setPipGeometry` action (task 1.2), which persists to localStorage on every call, is only ever invoked by the host in response to this single end-of-gesture callback, so it never fires mid-drag.
- Resize gesture: identical document-listener pattern, triggered from a single handle anchored bottom-right (`cursor-nwse-resize`), adjusting `width`/`height` (with `x`/`y` fixed) and enforcing `minWidth ?? 280` / `minHeight ?? 180` live during the drag, then clamping and committing once on release exactly like the drag gesture.
- Viewport re-clamp: register a `window.resize` listener while mounted that re-clamps the current `geometry` prop via `clampGeometry` and calls `onGeometryChange` with the result if it changed. ALSO run this same clamp pass once immediately on mount (not only on the `resize` event) â€” this is what self-corrects a persisted geometry that has gone stale (e.g. the browser window was resized while the app was closed) the moment the panel is first displayed, without requiring the state slice in task 1.2 to do any clamping of its own on hydrate.
- Chrome: `bg-card border border-border rounded-lg shadow-floating overflow-hidden` on the panel body; entrance/exit is a ~150ms ease-out fade+scale with no bounce (use `motion`'s `AnimatePresence`/`motion.div` with an `ease: [0, 0, 0.2, 1]`-style easing curve, matching the floating-chrome entrance already used in `apps/client/src/App.tsx:131-134`, or an equivalent CSS transition â€” pick one and keep it internally consistent).
- Accessibility: `role="complementary"`, `aria-label={title}` on the root; Escape must NOT close the panel â€” do not wire any `keydown` listener to `onClose` (the panel is non-modal, ideation decision D8).
- shadcn conventions: `data-slot="floating-panel"` on the root element, `cn()` (from `@/layers/shared/lib`) to merge `className` last so callers can override, a plain `ref` prop if a ref is needed internally (no `forwardRef` â€” React 19 convention per `.claude/rules/components.md`), and TSDoc on the exported component, both interfaces, and `clampGeometry`.

Barrel export: add `export { FloatingPanel, clampGeometry } from './floating-panel';` and `export type { FloatingPanelProps, FloatingPanelGeometry } from './floating-panel';` to `apps/client/src/layers/shared/ui/index.ts`, alongside the existing alphabetically-adjacent exports.

Unit tests at `apps/client/src/layers/shared/ui/__tests__/floating-panel.test.tsx` (RTL + jsdom per `.claude/rules/testing.md`) covering:
- renders `children` and the `title`
- dragging the header (synthetic `pointerdown` on the header, `pointermove`+`pointerup` dispatched on `document`) calls `onGeometryChange` exactly once with the final, moved geometry
- resizing from the bottom-right handle calls `onGeometryChange` with `width`/`height` no smaller than `minWidth`/`minHeight` even when the synthetic drag would shrink it further
- a geometry prop placed outside the mocked viewport bounds is clamped back on a simulated `window.resize` event (fire the event, assert `onGeometryChange` is called with an in-bounds result) AND on initial mount with an already out-of-bounds geometry prop
- the close control's click calls `onClose`
- the restore control is absent from the DOM when `onRestore` is omitted, and calls `onRestore` on click when provided
- `role="complementary"` and `aria-label` equal to `title` are present; both icon controls have `aria-label`
- a `keydown` event with `key: 'Escape'` does NOT call `onClose`

Create the state slice at `apps/client/src/layers/shared/model/app-store/app-store-pip.ts`, composed into `useAppStore` (`app-store.ts`), mirroring the composition pattern of `app-store-canvas.ts`/`app-store-right-panel.ts`.

Export exactly this shape verbatim:

```ts
/** Serializable descriptor â€” never a React node (ideation D4). */
export type PipContent = { kind: 'demo'; title: string };
// DOR-297 adds { kind: 'mcp_app'; sessionId; serverName; uri; title }
// DOR-298 adds { kind: 'widget'; sessionId; ... }

export interface PipSlice {
  pipContent: PipContent | null;
  pipGeometry: FloatingPanelGeometry | null; // null â†’ default dock bottom-right
  openPip: (content: PipContent) => void; // replaces current content (D3)
  closePip: () => void;
  setPipGeometry: (g: FloatingPanelGeometry) => void; // persists
}
```

`FloatingPanelGeometry` is a type-only import from `@/layers/shared/ui` (task 1.1's barrel export) â€” this is a legal same-layer cross-import (shared/model importing a type from shared/ui; `.claude/rules/fsd-layers.md` only restricts shared from importing entities/features/widgets, not its own sibling submodules).

Wiring:
- `apps/client/src/layers/shared/lib/constants.ts`: add `PIP_PANEL_STATE: 'dorkos-pip-panel-state'` to the `STORAGE_KEYS` const object, next to `RIGHT_PANEL_STATE`/`RIGHT_PANEL_LAYOUTS`.
- `apps/client/src/layers/shared/model/app-store/app-store-helpers.ts`: add `readPipGeometry(): FloatingPanelGeometry | null` and `writePipGeometry(g: FloatingPanelGeometry): void`, using the exact try/catch localStorage JSON read/write pattern already used by `readRightPanelState`/`writeRightPanelState` (lines 236-251) â€” read returns `null` on missing/corrupt data, write silently swallows quota errors.
- `createPipSlice`: `pipContent` starts `null`. `pipGeometry` hydrates from `readPipGeometry()` at slice creation, UNCLAMPED â€” clamping-on-display is the primitive's job (task 1.1's mount-time clamp effect), not the slice's, so a stale off-screen geometry self-corrects the instant the panel renders rather than the slice duplicating the same clamp math. `openPip(content)` unconditionally replaces `pipContent` (single-instance replace-on-open, decision D3 â€” no dedup/queue, unlike canvas's per-source-key dedup in `app-store-canvas.ts`). `closePip()` sets `pipContent` to `null` and leaves `pipGeometry` untouched (position survives close/reopen). `setPipGeometry(g)` sets `state.pipGeometry = g` AND calls `writePipGeometry(g)` â€” every call persists, so the only caller must be the host wiring the primitive's single end-of-gesture `onGeometryChange` callback (tasks 1.1/2.1's contract) â€” never call it per-frame.
- `apps/client/src/layers/shared/model/app-store/app-store-types.ts`: add `import type { PipSlice } from './app-store-pip';` and extend `export type AppState = CoreSlice & PanelsSlice & PreferencesSlice & CanvasSlice & RightPanelSlice & PipSlice;`, plus a line in the file's dependency-order comment block (mirroring the existing `app-store-canvas â†’ app-store-helpers` style entries).
- `apps/client/src/layers/shared/model/app-store/app-store.ts`: import `createPipSlice` from `./app-store-pip` and add `...createPipSlice(...a),` to the composed-slices block (after `...createRightPanelSlice(...a),`); update the module-level TSDoc slice list (lines 4-9) to add a `PipSlice` bullet describing the floating PIP panel state.
- `resetPreferences()` in `app-store.ts` (~lines 201-232): add `localStorage.removeItem(STORAGE_KEYS.PIP_PANEL_STATE);` to the removal block, and `pipContent: null, pipGeometry: null,` to the final `set({...})` call, mirroring the existing `rightPanelOpen: false, activeRightPanelTab: null, rightPanelLayoutKey: null,` lines.
- `apps/client/src/layers/shared/model/index.ts`: add `export type { PipContent } from './app-store/app-store-pip';` next to the existing `export type { CanvasDocument, BrowserHistoryState } from './app-store/app-store-canvas';` line, so consumer features (task 2.1's `PipHost`, and DOR-297/298 later) can import the union from the barrel instead of reaching into the slice file directly.

Unit tests at `apps/client/src/layers/shared/model/app-store/__tests__/app-store-pip.test.ts`, following `app-store-right-panel.test.ts`'s `localStorage.clear()` + `useAppStore.setState({...defaults})` `beforeEach` pattern (lines 11-19):
- `openPip` sets `pipContent` to the given descriptor
- `openPip` called a second time with different content REPLACES `pipContent` (no stacking, no dedup)
- `closePip` sets `pipContent` to `null` and does not change `pipGeometry`
- `setPipGeometry` updates `state.pipGeometry` and writes the identical value as JSON to `localStorage.getItem('dorkos-pip-panel-state')`
- a geometry value pre-seeded into `localStorage` under the `PIP_PANEL_STATE` key is reflected in the slice's initial `pipGeometry` at store construction (hydration)
- `resetPreferences()` (via `useAppStore.getState().resetPreferences()`) clears both `pipContent` and `pipGeometry` to `null` and removes the `dorkos-pip-panel-state` localStorage key
- after several `openPip` calls, `pipContent` never appears in any localStorage key â€” assert the persisted `PIP_PANEL_STATE` value only ever contains `{x, y, width, height}` shaped data, proving content is never persisted
